IF program exists in directory THEN

    Execute the program.

ELSE

    Return that the program cannot be found.
    Ask if user wants to look for the program manually to remember a future path.
    IF yes THEN
    
        Open explorer and wait for the user to type in or find the path.
        Save the path in a file with all user-determined paths.
        Open the program.
        
    ELSE
    
        Say "okay".
        End command.
        
    ENDIF
    
ENDIF
